text:
The board of trustees shall consist of seven members as follows:
     (1)  The director of human resources development of the State who shall serve as its chairperson;
     (2)  The director of finance of the State or a designated representative, ex officio;
     (3)  Five other persons, three of whom shall be public employees and represent employee interests. [L Sp 1981 1st, c 7, pt of §1; am L 1988, c 287, §2; am L 1994, c 56, §21]
